{% extends "base.jinja" %}

{% set title = "Welcome to mongo_objects" %}


{% block content %}
<h1 class="mt-4">{{ title }}</h1>
<div class="my-2">
<p>This sample Flask application manages ticket sales to imaginary events
to demonstrate the features of the
<a href="https://mongo-objects.headwaters.com.sg/" class="code" target="_blank">mongo_objects</a> Python module.</p>
<p>See the <a href="https://mongo-objects.headwaters.com.sg/en/latest/sample.html" target="_blank">Sample Application</a>
instructions for guidance in exploring this app.</p>
</div>

<div class="my-2">
<h2 class="mt-4">Module Features</h2>
<p><span class="code">mongo_objects</span> allows MongoDB documents to be managed as user-defined
<a href="https://mongo-objects.headwaters.com.sg/en/latest/MongoUserDict.html" class="code" target="_blank">MongoUserDict</a>
subclasses of <span class="code">UserDict</span> instead of as just plain dictionaries.</p>

<p><span class="code">mongo_objects</span> also provides proxy objects to manages the
subdocuments within each document, whether single dictionaries
(<a href="https://mongo-objects.headwaters.com.sg/en/latest/MongoSingleProxy.html" class="code" target="_blank">MongoSingleProxy</a>),
dictionaries of dictionaries
(<a href="https://mongo-objects.headwaters.com.sg/en/latest/MongoDictProxy.html" class="code" target="_blank">MongoDictProxy</a>),
or lists of dictionaries
(<a href="https://mongo-objects.headwaters.com.sg/en/latest/MongoListProxy.html" class="code" target="_blank">MongoListProxy</a>).</p>
</div>

<div class="my-2">
<h2 class="mt-4">Using The Sample App</h2>
<p>The application had two modes. <a href="{{ url_for('adminEventList') }}">Admin mode</a>
allows you to schedule events, add venue information, create multiple types of tickets
and review the tickets sold.</p>
<p><a href="{{ url_for('customerEventList') }}">Customer mode</a> allows imaginary
customers to purchase the various types of tickets.</p>
<p>Switch between modes using the navigation bar menu.</p>
</div>
{% endblock %}
